- Badges: counts and alerts in neutral or accent red

Design Philosophy:
- Modern, minimal, high-contrast for critical data
- Developer-focused with dense panels and fast navigation
- Clarity, traceability, and control with auditability and reversibility
- Legibility, depth, restrained accents, and consistency
- UX goals: quick scanning, reliable automation exposure, and human-in-the-loop control

Connected Pages and Features:
- Connected Page: Project Detail
- Connected Features: Project Management Automation (roadmaps, ticket automation, PR summarization, release notes, CI/CD integrations)

Notes on Implementation Safety
- FOLLOW the CRITICAL runtime safety rules in all code generation:
  - Supabase results use data ?? [] pattern
  - Guard array methods with Array.isArray or (items ?? []).map(...)
  - Initialize arrays with useState<Type[]>([])
  - Validate API shapes via Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
  - Use optional chaining for nested API data
  - Destructure with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

Deliverables
- A complete, ready-to-implement development prompt that can be used by an AI development tool to scaffold both frontend and backend for the Projects Dashboard, Project Detail, and the associated automation integration points.
- Include explicit data models, API contracts, UI component specs, and runtime safety guardrails embedded into code templates or pseudocode as appropriate for the target stack.

If you want, I can tailor this prompt further to your preferred tech stack (e.g., Next.js + Prisma, React + Redux, NestJS, PostgreSQL, Supabase-like layer) or provide starter code skeletons aligned to your conventions.

